    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A single-page, multi-section layout is chosen for its intuitive, scroll-based navigation that feels like a natural progression through a story. It starts with a strong hero section (Summary), moves to a visual timeline for career/education (Experience & Education), then to an interactive skills dashboard (Skills). This structure allows users to get a quick overview and then dive deeper into specific areas without leaving the page, making it more engaging than a static document. The flow is designed to guide the user from a high-level summary to detailed, interactive evidence of capabilities. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Summary: Report Info -> Professional Overview -> Goal: Inform -> Presentation: Dynamic Text Block -> Interaction: None -> Justification: Provides an immediate, high-level introduction.
        - Experience/Education: Report Info -> Career/Education History -> Goal: Show Change/Progression -> Presentation: Vertical Timeline (HTML/CSS) -> Interaction: Hover effects on timeline items -> Justification: A timeline is a highly intuitive way to visualize career progression and educational milestones chronologically.
        - Skills: Report Info -> Technical/Soft Skills List -> Goal: Compare/Organize -> Presentation: Interactive Radar Chart (Chart.js) & Grouped Lists -> Interaction: Buttons to switch between different skill charts (e.g., Networking, Data Analysis) -> Justification: A radar chart provides a compelling visual summary of proficiency across different domains, while interactive buttons allow users to explore specific skill sets in more detail, making a dense list of skills digestible and engaging.
        - Contact: Report Info -> Contact Details -> Goal: Action -> Presentation: Clickable Icons/Links -> Interaction: Click to email/visit profile -> Justification: Provides clear, actionable links for follow-up. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
